 By Sola Ogundipe The Federal government must change its current focus on the treatment and cure of diseases and, rather, embrace the practice of taking care of the overall wellness of Nigerians if the currently poor health indices of the country are to improve. Prof Frances Ajose, who gave the assertion ahead of her investiture as the 22nd President of the Medical Women’s Association of Nigeria, MWAN, Lagos State branch, argued that Nigeria as a country must become more pragmatic in resolving nagging health problems bedeviling its populace. Continue reading FG should focus more on wellness, less on disease — MWAN President at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard